  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA273-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉatu varavuṇarntu talaimakaṭku uraippāḷāy “niṉ vēṟupāṭu tāykkup pulaṉāka avaḷ vēlaṉaik kūvi veṟi ayarum” eṉpatupaṭac colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante said, as one who is talking to HER, after having understood HIS coming: “as your changes are within the knowledge of [your] mother, she calls the spear-bearer [and] prepares for the Veṟi [dance]”.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA273">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            iḵtevaṉ kollō tōḻi meyparan</l>
<l>            tevvaṅ kūrnta vēmuṟu tuyaram</l>
<l>            vemmaiyiṟ ṟāṉvarut tuṟīi namvayi</l>
<l>            ṉaṟiyā tayarnta vaṉṉaikku veṟiyeṉa</l>
<l>            vēla ṉuraikku meṉpava rākaliṉ </l>
<l>            vaṇṇa mikutta vaṇṇal yāṉai</l>
<l>            nīrko ṇeṭuñcuṉai yamaintuvārn tuṟainteṉ</l>
<l>            kaṇpō ṉīlan taṇkamaḻ ciṟakkuṅ</l>
<l>            kuṉṟa nāṭaṉai yuḷḷutoṟu</l>
<l>            neñcunaṭuk kuṟūumavar paṇputaru paṭarē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>What [is] this, friend,</l>
<l>[that] affliction his nature gives [us], which makes the heart tremble</l>
<l rend="indent">whenever it remembers the man from a land of hills,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the blue lotus, resembling my eyes,</l>
<l rend="indent2">is superiorily cool [and] fragrant,</l>
<l rend="indent2">the long mountain spring being in a quiet state of overflowing<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">amaintu vārntu uṟaintu</term>: what is the exact impact of this string?</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">with water,</l>
<l rend="indent3">as the majestic elephant whose colour is augmented<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">vaṇṇam mikutta</term>: T.V.G. interprets this strange phrase as the elephant being wholly black (due to his being submerged in water?).</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">since they say the spear-bearing [priest] will talk</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the Veṟi dance to mother who is [still] held in ignorance</l>
<l rend="indent3">as far as we are concerned, he having made us suffer the heat</l>
<l rend="indent3">of confused misery abounding in trouble, [pallor] spreading</l>
<l rend="indent3">on [our] body?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
